## 1. BACKEND DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n### Top-level contents of `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/`\n\n```\nbackend/\n├── jest-e2e.json\n├── node_modules/\n├── package-lock.json\n├── package.json\n├── src/\n├── test/\n└── tsconfig.json\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1A. Test Infrastructure (`backend/test/`)\n\n**Jest Config** (`jest-e2e.json`):\n- Test environment: `node`\n- Test regex: `test/e2e/.*\\.e2e-spec\\.ts$`\n- Transform: `ts-jest`\n- Module name mapper: `^src/(.*)$` → `<rootDir>/src/$1`\n\n**Test scripts in `package.json`:**\n```json\n\"test:e2e\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\",\n\"test:e2e:watch\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --watch --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\",\n\"test:e2e:cov\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --coverage --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\"\n```\n> NOTE: There are NO scripts for running unit tests (no `npm test`, no `npm run test` — only e2e scripts exist).\n\n**Test Setup Files:**\n- `backend/test/setup/test-app.factory.ts` — Creates a NestJS test app with an **in-memory SQLite database** (`better-sqlite3`). Registers all 9 entities. Configures global prefix `api`, global pipes (`ValidationPipe`), global filters (`AllExceptionsFilter`, `HttpExceptionFilter`), global interceptors (`LoggingInterceptor`, `TransformInterceptor`). Uses `synchronize: true, dropSchema: true` for a fresh DB each test run.\n- `backend/test/setup/test-database.ts` — `cleanDatabase()` deletes from all tables in reverse dependency order. `cleanTable()` for targeted cleanup.\n\n**Fixture Files:**\n- `backend/test/fixtures/user.fixture.ts` — Defines 4 test users: `renter`, `renter2`, `admin`, `suspendedRenter`. Provides `createTestUser()`, `seedTestUsers()`, `createUsers()`, `hashPassword()`, `TEST_PASSWORD`.\n- `backend/test/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts` — Mock JWT helpers: `generateAccessToken()`, `generateRefreshToken()`, `generatePasswordResetToken()` (all return mock token strings like `mock-access-token-{userId}-{role}`). `authHeader()`, `refreshCookieHeader()`, `authAndRefreshCookieHeader()` set cookie headers.\n- `backend/test/fixtures/property.fixture.ts` — 3 test properties: `downtownApt`, `suburbanHouse`, `cheapStudio`. `createTestProperty()`, `seedTestProperties()`. Also includes `testAmenities` (4 amenities: Parking, Gym, Pool, Pet Friendly) and `seedTestAmenities()`.\n\n**E2E Test Files (all marked as \"RED PHASE\" — tests define contract but modules don't exist yet):**\n1. `auth.e2e-spec.ts` (490 lines) — Tests for `POST /register`, `POST /login`, `POST /logout`, `POST /refresh`, `POST /forgot-password`, `POST /reset-password`, `GET /me`\n2. `profile.e2e-spec.ts` (176 lines) — Tests for `GET /profile`, `PATCH /profile`\n3. `properties.e2e-spec.ts` (757 lines) — Tests for `GET /properties` (search with pagination/filters/sorting), `GET /properties/:id` (detail), `POST /properties` (create admin-only), `PATCH /properties/:id` (update), `DELETE /properties/:id` (archive), `POST /properties/:id/photos` (upload), `DELETE /properties/:id/photos/:photoId`, `PATCH /properties/:id/photos/:photoId/primary`, `PATCH /properties/:id/photos/reorder`\n4. `favorites.e2e-spec.ts` (299 lines) — Tests for `GET /favorites`, `POST /favorites`, `DELETE /favorites/:propertyId`\n5. `inquiries.e2e-spec.ts` (499 lines) — Tests for `POST /properties/:id/inquiries`, `GET /inquiries`, `GET /inquiries/:id`, `PATCH /inquiries/:id/read`, `POST /inquiries/:id/respond`\n6. `amenities.e2e-spec.ts` (354 lines) — Tests for `GET /amenities`, `POST /amenities`, `PATCH /amenities/:id`, `DELETE /amenities/:id`\n7. `admin-dashboard.e2e-spec.ts` (164 lines) — Tests for `GET /admin/dashboard`\n8. `admin-users.e2e-spec.ts` (360 lines) — Tests for `GET /admin/users`, `GET /admin/users/:id`, `PATCH /admin/users/:id/status`\n\n---\n\n### 1B. Modules Under `backend/src/modules/`\n\n**CRITICAL FINDING: There are NO controller files, NO service files, NO module files, and NO DTO files yet.** The `backend/src/modules/` directory contains ONLY entity files. The project is in the \"RED PHASE\" of TDD — tests exist, entities exist, but the actual NestJS controllers/services/modules/DTOs have NOT been implemented.\n\n**Entities that exist (9 total):**\n\n| Module | Entity File |\n|--------|------------|\n| users | `user.entity.ts` |\n| auth | `refresh-token.entity.ts` |\n| auth | `password-reset-token.entity.ts` |\n| properties | `property.entity.ts` |\n| properties | `property-photo.entity.ts` |\n| properties | `amenity.entity.ts` |\n| properties | `property-amenity.entity.ts` |\n| favorites | `favorite.entity.ts` |\n| inquiries | `inquiry.entity.ts` |\n\n---\n\n### 1C. Entities (Detailed)\n\n**User** (`users.user.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `name`, `email` (unique), `password`, `phone` (nullable), `role` (RoleEnum, default 'renter'), `status` (UserStatusEnum, default 'active'), `emailVerifiedAt` (nullable)\n- Relations: OneToMany → `refreshTokens`, `resetTokens`, `favorites`, `inquiries`\n\n**RefreshToken** (`auth.refresh-token.entity.ts`) — does NOT extend BaseEntity:\n- Fields: `id`, `userId`, `token`, `expiresAt`, `revokedAt`, `createdAt`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → User\n\n**PasswordResetToken** (`auth.password-reset-token.entity.ts`) — does NOT extend BaseEntity:\n- Fields: `id`, `userId`, `token`, `expiresAt`, `usedAt`, `createdAt`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → User\n\n**Property** (`properties.property.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `title`, `description`, `price`, `bedrooms`, `bathrooms`, `squareFeet`, `propertyType` (PropertyTypeEnum), `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, `addressState`, `addressZipCode`, `addressLatitude`, `addressLongitude`, `availableFrom`\n- Relations: OneToMany → `photos`, `propertyAmenities`, `favorites`, `inquiries`\n\n**PropertyPhoto** (`properties.property-photo.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `propertyId`, `url`, `isPrimary`, `sortOrder`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → Property\n\n**Amenity** (`properties.amenity.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `name` (unique), `icon`\n- Relations: OneToMany → `propertyAmenities`\n\n**PropertyAmenity** (`properties.property-amenity.entity.ts`) — composite PK, does NOT extend BaseEntity:\n- Fields: `propertyId`, `amenityId`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → Property, ManyToOne → Amenity\n\n**Favorite** (`favorites.favorite.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `userId`, `propertyId`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → User, ManyToOne → Property\n- Unique index on `(userId, propertyId)`\n\n**Inquiry** (`inquiries.inquiry.entity.ts`) — extends `BaseEntity`:\n- Fields: `propertyId` (nullable), `userId` (nullable), `name`, `email`, `phone`, `message`, `status` (InquiryStatusEnum), `response`, `respondedAt`\n- Relations: ManyToOne → Property (SET NULL), ManyToOne → User (SET NULL)\n\n---\n\n### 1D. Base Classes (`backend/src/core/base/`)\n\n5 files with barrel export `index.ts`:\n\n**BaseEntity** — Provides `id` (UUID PK), `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` (soft delete). All timestamps auto-managed by TypeORM decorators.\n\n**BaseRepository** — Provides: `findAll()`, `findById()`, `findOne()`, `create()`, `update()`, `softDelete()`, `delete()`, `count()`. Wraps TypeORM `Repository<T>`.\n\n**BaseService** — Provides: `findByIdOrFail()` (throws NotFoundException), `findAll()`, `create()`, `update()`, `remove()` (soft delete), `delete()` (hard delete). Also supports `defaultRelations`.\n\n**BaseController** — Provides full CRUD endpoints: `POST /`, `GET /`, `GET /:id`, `PATCH /:id`, `DELETE /:id`. Includes Swagger decorators, pagination via `page`/`limit` query params, `ParseUUIDPipe` on `:id` params.\n\n---\n\n### 1E. Enums (`backend/src/common/enums/`)\n\n| File | Enum | Values |\n|------|------|--------|\n| `role.enum.ts` | RoleEnum | `RENTER = 'renter'`, `ADMIN = 'admin'` |\n| `user-status.enum.ts` | UserStatusEnum | `ACTIVE = 'active'`, `SUSPENDED = 'suspended'` |\n| `property-type.enum.ts` | PropertyTypeEnum | `APARTMENT`, `HOUSE`, `CONDO`, `TOWNHOUSE`, `STUDIO` |\n| `inquiry-status.enum.ts` | InquiryStatusEnum | `NEW = 'new'`, `READ = 'read'`, `RESPONDED = 'responded'` |\n\n---\n\n### 1F. Core Infrastructure (`backend/src/core/`)\n\nBeyond base classes, the full core infrastructure exists:\n\n- **Decorators**: `current-user.decorator.ts`, `public.decorator.ts`, `roles.decorator.ts`, `api-swagger.decorator.ts`, `api-response-data.decorator.ts`\n- **Filters**: `all-exceptions.filter.ts`, `http-exception.filter.ts`\n- **Guards**: `jwt-auth.guard.ts`, `jwt.strategy.ts`, `roles.guard.ts`\n- **Interceptors**: `logging.interceptor.ts`, `transform.interceptor.ts`, `set-token.interceptor.ts`, `remove-token.interceptor.ts`\n- **Pipes**: `validation.pipe.ts`\n\n---\n\n### 1G. Database Migrations\n\n`backend/src/database/migrations/001-initial-schema.ts` — A comprehensive migration (295 lines) that creates all 9 tables with proper columns, indexes, and foreign keys. Creates tables in dependency order: users → refresh_tokens → password_reset_tokens → properties → property_photos → amenities → property_amenities → favorites → inquiries.\n\n---\n\n## 2. MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml\n\n**File does NOT exist.** A glob search for `.claude-project/nestfind/status/MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml` returned no results anywhere in the project.\n\n---\n\n## 3. PROJECT_API.md (Full Contents)\n\nLocated at `.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_API.md` (1621 lines). Defines the complete API contract:\n\n**Endpoints by domain:**\n- **Auth** (7 endpoints): `POST /auth/register`, `POST /auth/login`, `POST /auth/logout`, `POST /auth/refresh`, `POST /auth/forgot-password`, `POST /auth/reset-password`, `GET /auth/me`\n- **Profile** (2 endpoints): `GET /profile`, `PATCH /profile`\n- **Properties** (9 endpoints): `GET /properties` (search), `GET /properties/:id`, `POST /properties`, `PATCH /properties/:id`, `DELETE /properties/:id` (archive), `POST /properties/:id/photos`, `DELETE /properties/:id/photos/:photoId`, `PATCH /properties/:id/photos/:photoId/primary`, `PATCH /properties/:id/photos/reorder`\n- **Favorites** (3 endpoints): `GET /favorites`, `POST /favorites`, `DELETE /favorites/:propertyId`\n- **Inquiries** (5 endpoints): `POST /properties/:id/inquiries`, `GET /inquiries`, `GET /inquiries/:id`, `PATCH /inquiries/:id/read`, `POST /inquiries/:id/respond`\n- **Amenities** (4 endpoints): `GET /amenities`, `POST /amenities`, `PATCH /amenities/:id`, `DELETE /amenities/:id`\n- **Admin Dashboard** (1 endpoint): `GET /admin/dashboard`\n- **Admin Users** (3 endpoints): `GET /admin/users`, `GET /admin/users/:id`, `PATCH /admin/users/:id/status`\n\n**Total: 34 endpoints.** All responses follow a standard envelope: `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }`. Paginated endpoints return `{ items: [...], meta: { total, page, limit, totalPages } }`.\n\n**Auth:** Renter = `renter` role only. Admin = `admin` role only. Authenticated = any valid token. Public = no auth needed.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PROJECT_DATABASE.md (Full Contents)\n\nLocated at `.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md` (394 lines). Defines:\n\n- **9 entities** with complete schema, indexes, relationships\n- **4 enums**: RoleEnum, UserStatusEnum, PropertyTypeEnum, InquiryStatusEnum\n- **FK Summary**: 9 foreign key relationships with CASCADE/SET NULL\n- **Soft delete**: Enabled on users, properties, amenities. NOT on refresh_tokens, password_reset_tokens, favorites, inquiries, property_photos, property_amenities.\n- **Naming conventions**: Tables `snake_case` plural, columns `snake_case`, enums PascalCase + `Enum` suffix\n\n---\n\n## 5. E2E Test Generator Guide\n\nLocated at `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-generate-e2e-tests.md` (824 lines). Key content:\n\n- **Directory structure**: `test/e2e/`, `test/setup/`, `test/fixtures/`, `test/mocks/`\n- **Test patterns**: CRUD endpoints (BaseController), Role-Based Access, Admin-Only endpoints\n- **Fixture usage**: How to create users, generate tokens, use auth headers\n- **Mock patterns**: Creating mock services with `@Injectable()`, capturing data, using `.overrideProvider().useClass()`\n- **Smart detection rules**: When to generate complete vs skeleton tests\n- **Checklist**: Auth, authorization, validation, success, error, CRUD tests for every endpoint\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Guide\n\nLocated at `.claude/nestjs/guides/testing-guide.md` (240 lines). Covers:\n- Unit testing with mocked repositories\n- Integration testing with real database\n- Mocking strategies (mock services, mock PrismaService)\n- Test data management (setup/teardown)\n- Coverage targets: 70%+ unit, critical paths integration, happy paths e2e\n\n---\n\n## 7. Architecture Overview\n\nLocated at `.claude/nestjs/guides/architecture-overview.md` (840 lines). Core concepts:\n\n- **4-Layer Architecture**: Controller → Service → Repository → Entity, all extend base classes\n- **Request Lifecycle**: Middleware → Guards → Interceptors (before) → Pipes → Controller → Service → Repository → Interceptors (after) → Exception filters\n- **Base Classes Pattern**: Each layer extends a base class that provides automatic CRUD\n- **Directory Structure**: `core/` for framework code, `modules/` for features, `infrastructure/` for external services, `database/` for migrations/seeds\n- **PROHIBITED patterns**: No direct `@InjectRepository` in services, no direct `process.env`, no `createQueryBuilder` in services, must use `extends Base*` on all layers\n- **Module pattern**: 5 files per feature (entity, repo, service, controller, module) + dtos/ folder\n\n---\n\n## 8. Package.json Test Scripts\n\n```json\n\"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n\"build\": \"tsc\",\n\"test:e2e\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\",\n\"test:e2e:watch\": \"...\",\n\"test:e2e:cov\": \"...\"\n```\n**No unit test scripts exist** (`npm test`, `npm run test`, etc.). Only e2e test scripts are configured.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Status Files (`.claude-project/nestfind/status/`)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `PIPELINE_STATUS.md` | Main pipeline tracker. **Backend phase = FAILED** (3/16 nodes). Database phase = Complete (1.00). Design = Complete. Frontend = Pending. |\n| `BACKEND_TESTS_GENERATED.md` | Reports 13 test files generated covering 34 endpoints across auth, profile, properties, favorites, inquiries, amenities, admin. Marked \"phase: backend-red\". |\n| `DATABASE_SCHEMA_REPORT.md` | Reports 9 entities, 1 migration, 9 relations, 4 enums, typecheck PASS. |\n| `DESIGN_STATUS.md` | Design approved, variation A (Dark Tech/Linear). |\n| `DESIGN_FULL_GENERATION_REPORT.md` | 16 HTML screens generated. |\n| `INIT_REPORT.md` | 7 directories created, pipeline status file created. |\n| `seed.yaml` | Project seed configuration defining roles, modules, flows, APIs, goals. |\n| `.blueprint-*.json` | Artifact metadata files for init, prd, design, database, user-stories, backend phases. |\n| `.gate-proofs/` | Gate validation proofs (init.proof, prd.proof, design.proof, database.proof, user-stories.proof). |\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY OF CURRENT STATE\n\nThis project is in the **RED PHASE of TDD for the backend**:\n- **Entities**: DONE (9 entities, all compiled and type-checked)\n- **Database Migration**: DONE (initial schema migration exists)\n- **E2E Tests**: DONE (13 test files covering all 34 API endpoints — these are RED/failing tests that define the API contract)\n- **Test Infrastructure**: DONE (test app factory, database cleanup, fixtures for users/auth/properties)\n- **Core Framework**: DONE (base classes, guards, decorators, filters, interceptors, pipes)\n- **Enums**: DONE (4 enums)\n- **Controllers/Services/Modules/DTOs**: NOT STARTED — these are the GREEN phase implementation that needs to be built to make the e2e tests pass\n- **Unit tests**: None exist, no unit test scripts configured\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1c00e5fd8ffeVx140qy7L9eaMz","sessionId":"ses_1c00e0490ffeIM6CuNTwP1362q","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"ope